root_causes: Validation as written will flag missing values even though the question is NotRequired. The sel if uses ~any(HidS4DE,1,2) which is true for missing values.
Script assumes test mode is indicated by qTesting = 1 (isTest() was the expected condition). If the actual test indicator variable or value differs, the condition will be incorrect.
instructions: Exclude missing values when validating a NotRequired question. Change the selection to require non-missing responses, e.g.: sel if qCountry = 7 & qTesting = 1 & ~miss(HidS4DE) & ~any(HidS4DE,1,2).

If your environment uses a different test-mode indicator than qTesting = 1, replace qTesting = 1 with the correct isTest() check or the appropriate variable/value (for example, use isTest() or qTesting <> 1 as applicable).
